      <section eId="sec_CC-3547">
        <num>CC 3547</num>
        <heading>3547.  Exceptional cases</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 3547.  Exceptional cases
The law applicable under Articles 3543-3546 shall not apply if, from the totality of the circumstances of an exceptional case, it is clearly evident under the principles of Article 3542, that the policies of another state would be more seriously impaired if its law were not applied to the particular issue.  In such event, the law of the other state shall apply.</p>
        </content>
